article.headline: Northeastern advances to 2K Sports regional final
article.linkText: Northeastern scores 2K Sports win against IUPUI
article.story: ANN ARBOR, Mich. -- Eugene Spates scored 14 points and Matt Janning added 13 in Northeastern's 73-60 victory over IUPUI Tuesday in a first-round game of the 2K Sports College Hoops Classic supporting Coaches vs. Cancer tournament. The Huskies (1-0) will play Michigan, a 77-55 winner over Michigan Tech, in Wednesday's regional final, while IUPUI (0-1) will play the Division II Huskies in the consolation game. Nkem Ojougboh added 12 points for Northeastern, while Chaisson Allen added 11. IUPUI's Robert Glenn led all scorers with 19 points off the bench and Alex Young added 17. The Jaguars hit just 2-of-17 3-point attempts. Spates hit 3-pointers on Northeastern's first two possessions, turning the second one into a four-point play. The Huskies led 17-8 midway through the first half and the Jaguars never seriously threatened in the final 30 minutes.
